- 10-year CAGR: ~10.4%
- 5-year CAGR (2020-2025): ~14.2%

**The ₹10,000/month for 20 Years Example:**
- SIP at 13%: ₹1.46 crore
- Gold at 10%: ₹76.5 lakh
- **SIP advantage: ₹70 lakh (92% more!)**

## Types of Gold Investment

### 1. Physical Gold (Jewellery / Coins / Bars)
- **Making charges:** 8-25% (jewellery), 1-3% (coins/bars)
- **Storage risk:** Theft, locker charges
- **Liquidity:** Moderate (takes time to sell)
- **Returns:** Base gold price minus making charges

### 2. Gold ETF
- **Expense ratio:** 0.5-1% annually
- **Purity:** 99.5% (no impurity risk)
- **Liquidity:** High (sell on exchange in seconds)
- **Tax:** 20% LTCG with indexation (held > 3 years)

### 3. Sovereign Gold Bond (SGB) - Best Option
- **Extra interest:** 2.5% per year on top of gold price appreciation
- **Tax on maturity:** COMPLETELY TAX-FREE (if held 8 years)
- **Annual interest:** Taxable as income
- **Minimum:** 1 gram; Maximum 4 kg/year
- **Government backed:** No credit risk

## Why Gold Belongs in Your Portfolio

Despite equity SIPs giving higher long-term returns, gold serves a unique purpose:

**Negative Correlation:** Gold rises when equities fall. During the 2008 crash, gold surged 25% while Sensex fell 52%. During 2020 COVID crash, gold rose 28% while equity fell 38%.

**Inflation Hedge:** Gold has maintained purchasing power over very long periods (decades to centuries). In currency debasement scenarios, gold protects wealth.

**Portfolio Diversification:** A portfolio with 10-15% gold historically shows lower volatility with minimal impact on long-term returns.

## Optimal Strategy: SIP + Gold Allocation

