## Duration Risk: Bonds vs CDs

CDs at banks: If you break early, you pay 3-12 months of interest penalty. Principal is always safe.

Treasury bonds (not T-Bills): If you sell before maturity on secondary market, you can lose principal if rates have risen. A 10-year bond bought at 4% loses ~8% of value if rates rise to 5%.

**For safety seekers:** T-Bills (under 1 year) or short-duration Treasuries avoid duration risk while giving state tax benefit.

