- Monthly expenses: £3,500/month = £42,000/year
- Less: Full State Pension £11,500/year
- From corpus: £30,500/year
- Retirement corpus: £30,500 × 25 = **£762,500**

## Inflation: The Hidden Retirement Risk

Using a 3% inflation rate, £3,500/month today costs £7,000/month in 24 years. Your retirement corpus calculation must account for this.

Rule of thumb: Multiply your retirement target by 1.5-2 if retirement is 20+ years away.

## Safe Withdrawal Rate in Different Environments

- 4% SWR: Historically sustainable for 30-year retirement (90%+ success)
- 3.5% SWR: 40-year horizon (FIRE movement standard)
- 3% SWR: Extremely conservative, near-100% success rate
- 5% SWR: Higher risk, suitable only with flexible spending plans

