## The 50/30/20 Rule: Budgeting Made Simple

Popularized by Senator Elizabeth Warren in her book "All Your Worth," the 50/30/20 rule divides after-tax income into three simple categories:

- **50% for Needs:** Rent/mortgage, utilities, groceries, insurance, minimum loan payments
- **30% for Wants:** Dining out, entertainment, subscriptions, shopping, holidays
- **20% for Savings & Investments:** Emergency fund, investments, debt repayment above minimum

## Worked Example: ₹80,000/month Take-Home (India)

| Category | Budget | Examples |
|----------|--------|---------|
| Needs (50%) | ₹40,000 | Rent ₹20K, groceries ₹8K, transport ₹5K, utilities ₹3K, insurance ₹4K |
